  "name": "Finger of Death",
  "ownership": {
    "default": 0
  },
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You send negative energy coursing through a creature that you can see within range, causing it searing pain. The target must make a Constitution saving throw. It takes [[/r 7d12 + 30]] necrotic damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p><p>A humanoid killed by this spell rises at the start of your next turn as a undead creature that is permanently under your command, following your verbal orders to the best of its ability. The animated target uses the Undead Creature's stat block.</p><p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 8th level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 2d12]] for each slot level above 7th.</p>",
